Output final answer with the format <<<answer>>>

from datetime import date, timedelta

# Function to find the last Tuesday of a given month and year
def last_tuesday(year, month):
    # Start from the last day of the month
    last_day = date(year, month + 1, 1) - timedelta(days=1) if month < 12 else date(year, 12, 31)
    
    # Go back to the last Tuesday
    while last_day.weekday() != 1:  # 1 corresponds to Tuesday
        last_day -= timedelta(days=1)
    
    return last_day.day

# Get the last Tuesday of March 2022
last_tuesday_march_2022 = last_tuesday(2022, 3)
last_tuesday_march_2022
